============================================================
  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     CNN
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Convolutional filters detect spatial features hierarchically
Year:        1989
Researchers: LeCun et al.
Applications:Image classification, object detection
Related:     Pooling, feature maps, ResNet

Concept:     Attention Mechanism
Category:    Mechanism
Definition:  Learns to focus on relevant input parts for each output
Year:        2015
Researchers: Bahdanau et al.
Applications:Machine translation, NLP, summarization
Related:     Self-attention, multi-head, cross-attention

Concept:     LSTM
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Gating mechanisms solve vanishing gradient in sequences
Year:        1997
Researchers: Hochreiter/Schmidhuber
Applications:NLP, speech, time series
Related:     GRU, RNN, gates, cell state

============================================================
  PHILOSOPHY
============================================================

Concept:      Existentialism
Branch:       Metaphysics
Definition:   Existence precedes essence; radical freedom and responsibility
Philosopher:  Jean-Paul Sartre
Example:      You are not born kind or cruel; you become so through choices

Concept:      Phenomenology
Branch:       Epistemology
Definition:   Philosophy must study first-person conscious experience directly
Philosopher:  Husserl/Heidegger
Example:      What is the structure of my experience of time or other people?

Concept:      Stoicism
Branch:       Ethics
Definition:   Focus only on what is in your control; accept all else with equanimity
Philosopher:  Marcus Aurelius/Epictetus
Example:      Illness is not in your control; your response to it is

